    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once softened, add 30g <span class=\"text-purple\">[45g]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[60g]</span> <strong>butter</strong> with 30g <span class=\"text-purple\">[45g]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[60g]</span> <strong>flour</strong> to the pan with the<strong> </strong>garlic and onion<strong> </strong>and stir with a wooden spoon for 3-4 min or until the butter melts and a sandy paste forms – this is your <strong>roux</strong></p><p>Gradually whisk 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[375ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[450ml]</span> <strong>milk</strong> into the roux, a little at a time and cook for 5 min or until a smooth, thick sauce remains – this is your <strong>béchamel sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
